{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f32285ce-70d1-45ea-b4c5-9869653a6813","content":"The directory appears empty, so I'll answer from my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk.\n\nTo switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you just need to **remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <!-- Remove or set to false: -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Why this is enough:** Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4+, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** runner. Setting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` was opting *out* of it. Removing that property opts you back in.\n\n**Other things to be aware of:**\n\n1. **CLI usage changes** — run tests with `dotnet test` as before, but you can also run the test executable directly (`./YourTests.exe`).\n2. **VSTest-specific adapters** — if you use `.runsettings` features or custom VSTest adapters, review compatibility. Most common settings (filters, loggers) work, but some need the new `--` arg syntax.\n3. **CI integration** — TRX logging is available via `--report-trx` (add the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package if not already pulled in by the SDK).\n\nIn short: delete the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` line and verify your tests still pass with `dotnet test`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4bdf7c11-187b-4573-bf5d-b85cca417e6f","outputTokens":406,"requestId":"286C:2B9ABB:161CFC4:1780CF8:6A045FD4"},"id":"3b4b9988-1c65-4484-ac91-3294d8ec641c","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:26:23.956Z","parentId":"bc49d59d-1cdf-43ec-9335-09d2194090bc"}
